<br>
Rhions statement is correct, people didn't have mana creation/donation in mind when creating their mage. But when push came to shove, and VI needed to 'conjure' up a role for our class on raids, they created a summoned item that was actually useful to many other classes. (remember that raids didn't exist when many people decided to become a mage, me included, birthdate 1/3/2000)<br>
<br>
From the EQ Manual:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Magician: The Magician is the summoner of the arcane arts, and can conjure up everything from a loaf of bread to a huge Fire Elemental to fight on his behalf. While not as offensively adept as a Wizard, a Magician still possesses considerable spell power. <br>
Modifiers: +10 Stamina, +10 Intelligence <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
 <br>
<br>
Our raid role quite clearly does align with our class definition. In fact our raid role probably aligns more closely with our class definition than many other classes. It might not be fun, but it is important, and I can't imagine being part of a CHeal chain would be all that exciting either. Raids are about TEAMWORK, everyone has a role, and for every class, that role can get repetitive.<br>
<br>
Too many people focus on the last line of our class definition which says 'a Magician still possesses considerable spell power.' This is a pretty subjective sentence, and people can agree or disagree if we still do possess considerable offensive spell power.<br>
<br>
If you created your magician with the intent of being something other than a summoner of the arcane, you should be flaming whomever gave you the idea to be a mage, not VI.<br>
<br>
You can point to any site you want that says otherwise, but the bottom line is those sites are merely 3rd party interpretations of what a mage should be. Not the official definition of our class as provided by the creators of the game.<br>
<br>
:shudders as she realizes she just defended VI<br>
<br>
From the player perspective, its a little different. If you're not having fun making rods when on a raid, and all you want to do is raid, here are your choices:<br>
<br>
1) quit eq. if you're not having fun, why are you playing the game?<br>
<br>
2) try another class<br>
<br>
3) scream 'nerf mod rod' and reduce the usefulness of our class, and the effectiveness of your guild.<br>
<br>
Sorry if any of this comes off as a bit harsh, but this topic is getting old.<br>
<br>
Improve our class with new spells (eg. summon stack o'mod rods, group summoning, etc), not nerfs......<br>
<br>
 <p>Naladini <BR>
Elementalist of the 52nd Season-Stormhammer<BR>
